1. BlockChain is a bunch of containers or blocks linked together in a chain.
   It is a ledger which is immutable, unable to tamper and decentralized.

2. Blockchain is mainly used to form a decentralized or a peer to peer network.
   It is trying to remove the centralized system and to implement unhackable and a transparent network.
   The major reason for the evolution is the International Bank crisis in 2008.

3. Immutable, Transparency, Verifiable, Unchangable, Distributed Network.

4. A Block contains - Block number, Transaction Records(Important Data), Previous Block Signature.

5. If the fingerprint of one block is changed, then the fingerprint of all the other blocks is also changes.
   Everyone on the network sees the same chain and then verifies chain is correct.
